ratings.rComments: You need to go to class to pass and get participation credit. Shes always there for you if you ask for help. I think she teaches pretty well.
Colleen is not a friendly outgoing teacher, but she gets the material across and teachers her students. If you pay attention in class, you'll learn the material.

WORST PROFESSOR I HAVE EVER MET. It's like she is trying to trick her students in every possible way on purpose. First time homework due on 5AM? !No announcements and reminders at all about pop quizzes?! Tests have much more difficult content (even brand new stuff) than homeworks?! Take her Econ202class and you will understand "desperate". CNMB.

She explains well. Gives more than enough of iclicker and homework points. Tests are indeed tricky but you can get a decent grade as long as you don't make any careless or conceptual mistakes. Know your content well and you should be fine. Her ppt is enough for both exam preparation and learning.

Here's a few things to take away:  1) This class is really hard, so study and know everything  2) She makes her tests tricky, with "None of the Above" options, which is why the averages on tests are low 3) It is possible to get an A. I did, and I got a D on my first midterm  She curved the class by about 6-7% at the end of the semester.

No matter how much you study the material, she will always try and trick you on the exams. There were times when my T.A. didn't know the answer to some of the exam questions. I thought that was very unreasonable. Overall, if you study enough, it should not be too hard to pull off a B.

I would avoid at all costs. The material isn't extremely tough, but she plays so many tricks on her exams that it's almost impossible to get an A, not unless you spend your entire life reading the chapters and continually practicing problems. This will be my first B I've ever gotten.

The material isn't impossible and stats can be interesting. Colleen made the exams consist of only challenging problems and did not focus on us understanding the material. Also, she throws in a lot of last minute curveballs (i.e. she changed our test from mult choice to free response on the day of the exam).   Overall good lectures, tough exams.
She teaches and explains everything well. However, it is very hard to get an A.
Never have a teacher meaner than her
Many mistakes in homework and exams
8 AM Quizzes

Although the material is not too bad to learn, the exams (which make up 85% of your grade) are filled with tricks that are sure to fool anybody. No matter how well I knew the material, I still managed to fall for her tricks on each exam!

This class has been the hardest class I've ever taken. It sucks because you are required to take it as a business major and she's the only professor. They intentionally make the midtermsexams very difficult so do not underestimate them!
SOOOOOOOOOOOOO BAD! I wish I had taken Stats100 instead of this class

you get iclicker points for going to class but she isn't a very good teacher. you are really going to be on your own in this class so find a helpful group to study with. luckily the material isn't difficult at all

Colleen Schultz is easily the worst professor at the University of Illinois. It's a disgrace she's allowed to continue to teach. She doesn't explain anything, but magically expects you to know everything she never even mentioned to you on the test. Homework doesn't even help. Avoid her at all possible costs.

There are only four tests in the whole semester and she doesn't give you much opportunity to buffer your test scores. Lectures are not clear and she doesn't teach you everything that's on the test. She throws a lot of curve balls on the tests and she requires you to do your work out at the sixth decimal place which leaves large margin for error.

Where do I even start? iClickers everyday sucked ass especially at 8AM. She is very lazy and makes no effort to help her students directly. She doesn't have office hours - NOOO that lowly task is for TA's according to her (I probably learned more from them than her). Even in emails she says go to office hours instead of  actually helping

Schultz is a good teacher. Make sure you go to class and do the aplia assignments. The tests are easy, but the final is more difficult. The curve at the end is very high. I got an 87 and that ended up being an A.

TAKE STAT 100 INSTEAD!!!!!! do not take econ 202 with her, shes a good enough teacher but her class is 90% tests and the tests are hard. Stat 100 covers the same credit and its 10x easier. Schultz is actually a good teacher  but she makes her class impossible to get a good grade in, save yourself the time and effort and dont take it.

Colleen does a poor job on accurately testing students for the subject matter learned in class. She generally carries herself with a poor attitude in class, and seems to be irritated when students ask questions. She does not appear to be passionate about teaching.

Worst professor I had so far at UIUC. Tricky exam questions and unhelpful TA sections. The final is not fair, and the questions are not hard, but very confusing. Whatever, you can not avoid her since only she teaches econ202 for years. Bear with it!

Colleen is the worst professor I've had at U of I. She tries to trick you with her exams and makes statistics much more difficult than it has to be.  I learned more by myself than from her. It's a shame that this course is required for business majors.

Quite horrible professor. You need to be in class as much of the material is out of order or not presented in the book in the same manner that is presented in class. She also uses the iClicker system for points every class period. She will try to play tricks on exams, and doesn't allow audio recording. Doesn't post answers to PP slides if you miss.
Although she can be crabby and boring she is amazing at explaining things clearly.  Go to class, pay attention, and you'll get a good grade.  Her grading policy is very student friendly and fair.

The class itself was average as far as difficulty. The best way to learn the material is by going to lecture. The tests can be a bit tricky. I don't know if this is typical or if I just got lucky but at the end of the semester she pretty much threw points out for free to the whole class. Overall she's alright.

I hate this professor.. She was awful and her tests were the trickiest test I've ever seen. Horribly boring lectures. She is extremely sarcastic when you go to her for help. Avoid her at all costs. She is terrible

While the material itself is really easy, Schultz makes the exams as tricky as possible. Class is pretty boring, but can be helpful. The final was optional which was nice. Overall, it is very easy to get a B, but don't expect an A without a lot of studying, despite the easiness of the material.

Exams may be tricky, but they aren't terrible as long as you attend lectures and do all the homework. You should make sure you understand all the homework problems and the trickiest problems because they will always appear on exams. Easy A or B. Anything less is because you didn't understand all the concepts taught or in the homework.
Some questions in the exams are tricky. But generally the class is easy. The professor is kind of lazy.

Agree with below. This is an easy A class if you pay attention to in-class problems and do your hw. The in-class problems and practice tests resemble the actual tests, so just learn them well and you'll do great. On one of our midterms, 30% got perfect scores. Yes, seriously.
just not a fun person at all. no technology allowed in class, no laptops no phones out, can't use camera phone to take picture of a PP slide.

Seems like a bitter person. Also, she kept saying the hw is due wednesday but not the time. Turns out its due wednesday morning at 5 am hahahaha. I had not paid for the program yet as i registered for the course late. TA says she repeated the time many times which she did NOT.No lowest score drop policy so she is basically out to make life hell.
Her class is challenging, no doubt about it. Go to class everyday, pay attention and take good notes. Her exams can be hard, but if you study beforehand, you won't have a problem.

Relatively straightforward and helpful. I had a few questions and she was good about responding in a timely manner. My TA was also very helpful. She has clear and reasonable expectations, should not be too difficult if you are willing to put in the effort.
This professor is extremely tricky!!! I've been to the TA office hours and even the TAs can't solve her questions sometimes.
The class is a complete joke, but she is literally the WORST professor I've had on campus. She will definitely try to trick you on exams so be super careful when reading each question.

She has a very weird calculator policy, you can only use the 1$ basic calculator. She uses numbers with 6 decimals in her problems to her delight) and you have to do all the calculations with that calculator so if you hit a wrong button by mistake, you have to start all over. I hated every second of her class: useless, boring and uninteresting.

She at times seems uninterested, there are many tricks put on the test so make sure to review things from past exams because that always has a large enough impact on the following tests, the tests are not curved but the class is, if you put in the work to understand the material, you should do well.

Literally one of the easiest classes at this school. If you do not do well on the tests then that is your fault. You get a cheat sheet for every test and this class is all about knowing how to use the formulas given to you on the cheat sheet. Although she might not be the best professor, this class is easy.

Tests are not reflective of what you know in the class.  TA's are completely useless and can ruin your grade by giving you misinformation. By far one of my least favorite classes and I love economics.  Be sure to do well on the first test because it is the only one that is relatively straightforward.  The rest will not relate to what you learned.

For material that is not difficult and rather straightforward, she always finds a way to throw curveballs on exams that you are not prepared for at all. All multiple choice tests with answers within .0001 from each other. Exams are not indicative of whether you know the material. By far my least favorite class on campus so far.

Schultz's course isn't a walk in the park, but it isn't extremely difficult either. Great preparation for 203 with Petry. It's a statistics course so exams and problems are going to be inevitably tricky. If you take 203 and dislike it, then business or economics isn't for you. Good preparation to think quantitatively and critically.

Schultz is a completely awful professor. Do not take this class unless you really have to. I emailed her to ask about a test I took and it took four emails and two emails to the Econ department head before she replied. Additionally, it was incredibly snippy and condescending. Decent teacher; awful person.

My experience in her class has easily been the worst of any class I have taken at U of I. Her lectures leave you ill prepared for the exams and the TAs are completely incompetent. When I emailed her asking to meet with her, I ended up sending her four separate messages over 4 weeks before giving up and tracking her down after lecture. Unbelievable.

Great teacher. Go to class. Discussion was helpful sometimes. In discussion we either went over new material or it was a clarity/review type session. Do the hmwrk bc it helps a LOT.  If you do the hmwrk n understand it, u should do well on the tests
This class isn't all that bad.  The material is very straight forward.  Just make sure to always double check your work on the tests.  The homeworks help you prepare for the exams.

My TA was inept, but Prof Schultz did her job well.  Overall this class was relatively straightforward.  You get formula sheets, so every test is essentially open book and you have ample time for the 20 mc questions.
Terrible.  The material is straight forward and easy to learn on your own, she is useless.  Her exams are ridiculous, and not like the homework or examples you work in class.

Schultz just stands up on stage and reads off the power point slides.  You basically have to teach yourself everything and the exams can be pretty tricky.  It is a shame that there isn't another option for this course.  My only B in college.

Colleen has an attitude and is not a very nice person.  Her teaching style is lazy and careless. The course is set up so if you make tiny mistakes you will get significant points off. econ 202 caused me a lot of stress but i somehow got an A.  not looking forward to econ 203...although she doesnt teach it. thank god

Her teaching style is easy to follow, as all of her notes are given from her powerpoint lectures. Her tests are only 20 questions and some times tricky, making it difficult to get an A. Overall she is not a pleasant person, but if you attend lectures and do the homework it's not terrible.

A community college level professor teaching for a Big Ten University.This rushed course teaches on the same level as it confuses.The prof knows very little how to teach when away from her pre-made slides (wonder who made them for her)? Add that the TA's sometimes teach opposite what is taught in lecture. The whole course is economic diarrhea.

The class is straight forward so if you take the time outside of class to look over the material and get help from the TAs then you will be fine. She does her job of teaching the material and explaining it, along with answering any questions students might have.
Colleen is pretty good at teaching, very clear and concise with her explanations. Concise enough to get out of class early 90% time. She is kind of lazy though...

She is a very good lecturer and explains the material well if anyone has questions. The homework can sometimes be stressful because it requires precise answers due to mallards format. As for her exams, they are 20 question MC so it is difficult to get an A, however if you study and attend class this should breeze by as an easy B at least

Class material is simple if you attend lectures. But because of this the test material can be out to trick you at times. Colleen doesn't respond to emails, and doesn't care about students individually. She is also unavalible for office hours so if you don't understand something go to the TAs. You can still get an easy A or B despite her uselessness

i dont get how people say shes hard and useless. the class is VERY STRAIGHT FORWARD. all you do in class is do problems, which are the same as the exam. she also answered questions clearly. Lecture is not mandatory but useful and she usually let us out after 20 mins. if u didnt like this class your going to hate 203 and 302
One thing I noticed about her is that she has no office hours. The TAs are usually not competent enough to answer your questions.

Lectures and content of the class are very straightforward. Exams are bull. Seem easy but your grade depends on 19-20MC questions where there's much room for error esp using the one line calculators to calculate really long numbers, check and triple check your answers

Her lectures are good. Homework is pretty easy. Discussion is pointless to go to except to turn in homework. The class may start out seeming VERY easy, but the test are NOT. She can be very tricky on them & it's confusing. All the tests excluding the 2nd are somewhat hard. The 2nd midterm is VERY easy, but if you study hard, you'll be good.

Possibly one of the worst professors the University offers. Has a email policy set up to her advantage, if you don't send her an email the right way she doesn't have to answer back. This ultimately allows her infallibility if she forgets to respond to your email, she can claim you didn't write it the correct way. Terrible exams, No Compass grades.

She is very good at explaining the topic she teaches. Its a really easy class, but the tests are unfair. They are pretty easy and relate to the homework/material but are only 20 questions multiple choice. Its too hard to get an A on a short MC stats exam. There is too much room for error and she of course puts the tricks on the exams.

You get a sense that she is a good orator.Class is not too bad but exams can be challenging and you will never know how you you fare in the final. A radom grade that may or may not correspond with your earlier test scores is assigned in the end.Though if you have taken Gotheil, you will know that he does the same as well. Take STAT 100 if you can.

Honestly, I enjoyed her class probably one of the best profs I've had at this university, she knows her stuff. Yeah we're let out early 75% of the time but that's bc there's no reason to keep us longer. Exams are legit-based on hw & everything in notebook used in lecture. Go to class, or u won't understand the material! willing to help u if asked.

I had low expectations but have been pleasantly surprised how very effective a teacher she is.Extremely competent and forthright about the tests.Unlike Gotheil,she also did not force students to waste 150 bucks on self-written books. In fact none was required; we learned everything in class.  The class was not the easiest but not rigorous either.

Professor Schultz keeps things short and to the point. She tells you exactly what you need to know for the test, nothing more nothing less. We often get out early because she likes to keep the classes on the same pace and ours moves much faster for whatever reason. I would recommend her because she shows you exactly what you need to know.

She has abundant teachjing experience in Econ 202, which makes students understand things easy. In fact, materials you will cover are VERY easy. Attendance is strongly recommended. You need a TA for homework assignment. Exams are also easy, IF you study. People complaining her are either who love procrastination or just stupid.
No Comments

She should be teaching Let-Everyone-Go-Early 101 instead, since that's apparently what she specializes in. Seriously - I can't think of a day when we didn't get out at least 15 minutes early. Oh, and if you struggle in this class - all I have to say is: good luck in ECON203, which is a total LOL-fest.
easy to understand, class is not difficult, follow along and go to class and it will be easy

Honestly, despite the general consensus here, this class is EASY. What is more likely: that Schultz is a mean-spirited, incompetent demon trying to "trick" everyone, or that a vocal minority of students were over-confident in their skills prior to tests, and then realized that they either were not smart enough or did not study enough to get an A...

Actually, I did real well in the class and still feel like it was a dysfunctionally organized class from top to bottom. It was so bad that I remember she gave questions on tests she never went through in lecture or discussion or through announcements. SHE IS OUT TO TRICK YOU. Repetition is the key and practicing the online quizzes doesn't help.

If you complete the course packet in class and do the homework, then you should get an A (I got an A). DO NOT BLOW OFF STUDYING FOR THE FIRST 2 EXAMS. Put in 45 minutes to study for them cause they will keep your grade high since the 3rd exam is very difficult and the final is fairly difficult.

class is very easy, people that wrote underneath myself are just very incompetent and dont know what they are talking about, class is structured, hw is made difficult so you understand the material, repetition is key, more times you do something, better you get at it, take this class and do the hw dont listen to people who gave her bad ratings
They really need to restructure this class.  It is like a cattle call.  Hope you have a good TA because Schultz won't teach you anything.  She is an an absolutely horrible teacher.

Grades in this class are mostly determineed by the exams; Half of your grades on the exams are determined by what you know in statistics, and the other half is determined by your ability to outsmart Colleen's test architecture, which heavily punishes anyone who second-guesses themselves. Take ECON 202 elsewhere because UIUC's offering is very poor.

Not an organized class. The online quizzes are difficult b/c they are not multiple choice, you don't know what the real answers are, and questions are different each time.The tests are more difficult than they should be and she will put stuff on the test that she never went through in class. She doesn't even teach, anybody could instruct that class

I've gotten through Calc I & II but this class was ridiculous.  The exams are extremely hard & its not like a normal math class where u got a book to do practice problems; its just ur binder from class.  You get SOME online homework before quizes, but you have no way to know what you did wrong and correct it. Horribly organized class.

Schultz left mid semester to have her baby without telling us (and we didn't even know she was pregnant).  That was nice of her.  The class wasn't that bad.  I didn't find homework difficult, but the exams were really hard and didn't reflect the material always.  There was minimal out of class work.

You definately need to attend lecture and discussion to keep up. As long as you put in effort and keep up with the homework you shouldn't have any trouble. Homework is VERY ANNOYING but in the end helps with drilling some of the concepts into your head. Overall I enjoyed this class, and recommend it.

The homework is annoying and time consuming but overall this is the easiest class I have taken on campus/in the college of business. Does not require much time committment and the tests are very straight forward. She gives you a sheet with all the equations to use on exams.
If you go to class and do the (often frustrating) homework carefully this class really isn't that bad. The tests are tricky, but the course is curved very generously.
Easy material. She's clear about laying down what's expected of students on tests and what not. The online homework is ANNOYING! The class is on a curve.

This is a STAT course, with little relevance to Economics in general.  A few impossible questions on every exam.  I felt like we were expected to know things after little or no demonstration.  Schultz is really not a pleasant person to look at or listen to.  I put forth a decent amount of effort.  B for the class, but a 59 on the final...
That wasn't easy. That's for sure. If you take this class, GO TO lectures!!! Work hard and you'll do better than me.If you don't need this class don't take it as Gen ed or somth. It's tough.
Very thorough in class and explains things very well. Tests are little tough and you really need to understand the concepts to do well on them. I am anticipating an A in the class but I like Econ.
Nice lady, horrible exam.

I don't know what you all are talking about.. this is the easiest class I've taken at UofI. The only thing that would make this class remotely difficult is memorization of the formulas, but she gives you a formula sheet for each test with everything you need. Tests are very straightforward.
Very easy class... lecture helps, but come test time it is all about execution.
Fantastic teacher!  Highly recommended

worst teacher ever. she wants you to do poorly and her test reflect this. She was the first teacher I've ever had that actually curved grades so that they would hurt you. The most worthless woman in the world.

Seems nice in class but once test time comes, your opinion of her will change. TAs are either not proficient in English or not helpful and therefore useless in either case. There is no reference-based textbook for this class, so if you find yourself in a state of confusion, don't expect to be able to simply look it up later.
Terrible teacher. Overall she was not very helpful with regard to learning the material and tests are very hard.

202 focuses mostly on memorization of formulas and random definitions. I expected to be able to actually understand stats, but she introduces things without any comment on meaning. Tests are putative and don't cover the material fairly. No textbook exists that teaches it "her" way so you have to rely on the awful notes and braindead TAs.
this is a super easy class. its all formulas and study her notes and u will get an A. take her
Not recommended for your own good ...
She told me there was gonna be around 30 questions on the final...there ended up being 67 questions.  She never went over any of the crap on the test either...:(
Very hard, makes tests a lot harder than the material needs to be compared to what she taught in lectures.  TA's don't help much either.  Overall poor class.

i'd taken statistics before, and expected to breeze through this class. unfortunately this woman made things very difficult. she purposely tricks you on her tests and doesn't give you a clear idea of what's going to be on them. the icing on the cake is her beautiful singsong voice, which makes lecture soooo wonderful.
The material is easy, her tests are not.  The trickiest tests I've ever taken, the class set-up is awful.

the tests in this class are tricky as hell. you can make up for your grade with the homework somewhat. there was a big curve in the class too. the one problem is that colleen schultz is extremely hot and may distract both male and femalte students with her  excquisite beauty

In all my time being a student, I have not experienced a more arrogant, useless, and evil instructor as I did when I was in Colleen Schultz/Houlihan's class. It is a shame people like her are given a salary to teach. I want a refund.
I am the walrus...coo coo cachoooooooo!  This class isnt that hard, but the tests are complete bull**** compared to the homework

Unfortunately this class is required..if its not..dont take it! The exams are much harder than the lecture material so theres not much you can do. TAs are sometimes hard to understand so basically you are on your own.

SCHULTZIEEE.O I thought the class was REALLY easy, but the tests are TRICKY. She's arrogant, like knowing basic statistics makes her the "God of the Class." TheTAwas good,and she's won awards,butIfelt like it was a trip back to the bad highschool teacher that felt like she knew it all,but shedidn't.

Very hard teacher, TAs are just plain bad. Tests are designed to kill your grade. There's always a trick on a test that was never presented in class or in any other way, so you're totally on your own.

Class looked easy at the beginning. Then the first test came, and it was crap. You have to study and know what you are doing for this class. There is a good curve, but if you don't know the material backwards and forwards, you're screwed.

Prof. Schulz isn't at all friendly. Plus, she can't  explain things in simple English. You have to really know your stuff before the exams. Simply taking the practice quizzes won't cut it. You need to know how to handle all the problems, while also watching out for tricks and twists on the exams.

Prof. Schultz is a tough professor. She speaks very un-clearly in class and definitely doesnt explain things too well. You pretty much teach yourself the material, so going to class is pretty important, esp. for pop quizzes! Tests are difficult so study your butt off!
whats with this woman? i get an A on the first test and all of a sudden i feel like a chicken with my head cutoff, i know the material but tests are crap, and she's a total **** outside of class.
Worst prof. in the entire world.  Not very friendly, tests don't test what you know.  They are designed to fail you.  Have fun w/ this class.

I don't really like Econ, but she makes it fun and entertaining. //'tying rope around neck'// The exams are very easy.  //'climbing up on chair'// I love her and could be more pleased with the way she teaches. //'tying rope to fan'// Props to her.  //'kicked the chair out'//   Aaaghhh.
Seems to take pleasure in seeing students fail.  Test questions are designed to be missed.
Could care less about you and whether you learn or not. Unfortunately there's little choice in who to take this class with. TA's seem incompetent.

Exam points are strangely distributed; some questions seem trivial.  TA's are questionable - shouldn't the TA's teach the students, not vice versa?  Mallard quizzes can sometimes seem impossible - doesn't really follow the "recommended text"
I hate her.  I knew that material, yet bombed her bloody tests.  Schuuuuuuuuuuuuuuultz.

Go to lecture, definitely.  Questions are answered a little curtly.  Exams weren't too bad.  Lecture notes help, but if don't review them before a test, then good luck--sometimes feel you are on your own She does slow down if things are unclear.

I love her, great class notes.  TAs aren't the best, but what can you do.  Oh, and don't talk during her class--she HATES it!  She will stare you down until you shut up.  Just go to lecture every day and PAY ATTENTION and do the online quizzes.
